obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39702)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39702&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prisons Act,`
  line 1894.
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India except ^2[the territories which, immediately before the`
  line `1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States].]"`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of July, 1894.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this Act shall apply to civil jails in the ^3[State] of Bombay ^4[as it existed`
  line `immediately before the 1st November, 1956] outside the city of Bombay, and those jails shall`
  line `continue to be administered under the provisions of sections 9 and 16 (both inclusive) of ^5Bombay`
  line `Act 2 of 1874, as amended by subsequent enactments.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "province" which was subs. by the A O. 1948 for "presidency".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `5. The Civil Jails Act, 1874.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39703)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Repeal.] Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39703&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39704)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39704&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act`
  line
  line `(1) "prison" means any jail or place used permanently or temporarily under the general`
  line `or special orders of a State Government for the detention of prisoners, and includes all`
  line `lands and buildings appurtenant thereto, but does not include`
  line
  line `(a) any place for the confinement of prisoners who are exclusively in the custody of the police;`
  line
  line `(b) any place specially appointed by the State Government under section 541 of the ^1Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1882 (10 of 1882); or`
  line
  line `(c) any place which has been declared by the State Government, by general or special order, to`
  line `be a subsidiary jail;`
  line
  line `(2) "criminal prisoner" means any prisoner duly committed to custody under the writ,`
  line `warrant or order of any Court or authority exercising criminal jurisdiction, or by order of a`
  line `Court-martial ;`
  line
  line `(3) "convicted criminal prisoner" means any criminal prisoner under sentence of a Court or`
  line `Court-martial, and includes a person detained in prison under the provisions of Chapter VIII`
  line `of the ^1Code of Criminal Procedure, 1882 (10 of 1882), or under the ^2Prisoners Act, 1871 (5`
  line `of 1871) ;`
  line
  line `(4) "civil prisoner" means any prisoner who is not a criminal prisoner ;`
  line
  line `(5) "remission system" means the rules for the time being in force regulating the award of marks to,`
  line `and the consequent shortening of sentences of, prisoners in jail ;`
  line
  line `(6) "history-ticket" means the ticket exhibiting such information as is required in respect of each`
  line `prisoner by this Act or the rules thereunder ;`
  line
  line `(7) "Inspector General" means the Inspector General of Prisons ;`
  line
  line `(8) "Medical Subordinate" means an Assistant Surgeon, Apothecary or qualified Hospital`
  line `Assistant; and`
  line
  line `(9) "prohibited article" means an article the introduction or removal of which into or out of a prison`
  line `is prohibited by any rule under this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3, (9 of 1894).--In section 3 of the Prisons Act, 1894(9 of 1894)`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the said Act), for clause (5) the following clauses shall be substituted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) "remission system" means the system of regulating the award of marks to, and the`
  line `consequent shortening the sentences of prisoners in jail in accordance with the rules for the time`
  line `being in force;`
  line
  line `(5a) "furlough system" means the system of releasing prisoners in jail on furlough in`
  line `accordance with the rules for the time being in force."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 29 of 1958, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 3 of the Prisons Act, 1894 (IX of 1894), hereinafter to as the said Act, for clause (5), the following clauses shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) 'remission system' means the system of regulation the award of marks to, and the consequent shortening of sentence of, prisoners in jail in accordance with the rules for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(5A) 'furlough system' means the system of releasing prisoners in jail in furlough in accordance with the rules for the time being in force."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1953, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act IX of 1894.--In the Prisons Act, 1894 (hereinafter referred to as "the Principal Act"), in section 3, clause (8) shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `2. See now the Prisoners Act, 1900 (3 of 1900).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39705)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Accommodation for prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39705&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall provide, for the prisoners in`
  line `the territories under such Government, accommodation in prisons constructed and regulated in`
  line `such manner as to comply with the requisitions of this Act in respect of the separation of`
  line prisoners.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39706)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Inspector General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39706&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `An Inspector General shall be appointed for the territories subject to`
  line `each State Government, and shall exercise, subject to the orders of the State Government, the`
  line `general control and superintendence of all prisons situated in the territories under such`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39707)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Officers of prisons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39707&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `For every prison there shall be a Superintendent, a Medical Officer`
  line `(who may also be the Superintendent), a Medical Subordinate, a Jailer and such other officers as the State`
  line `Government thinks necessary :`
  line
  line `Provided that ^1[the State Government of Bombay] may ^2*** declare by order in writing that in any`
  line `prison specified in the order the office of Jailer shall be held by the person appointed to be`
  line Superintendent.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 6 of the principal Act shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section.`
  line
  line `(2) In sub-section (1) so renumbered--`
  line
  line `(a) after the words "a Superintendent" the brackets and words "(who may be a Deputy Inspector-General of Prisons" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(b) the words "a Medical Subordinate" shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(c) after the said sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Where one or more Deputy Superintendents are appointed for a prison, they shall, subject to the general or special orders of the Inspector-General, exercise, carry out or discharge all or any of the powers, duties and functions of a Superintendent under this Act, or any law for the time being in force, as the Superintendent may delegate to them."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "the Governor of Bombay in Council".`
  line
  line `2. The words "with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C." omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39708)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Temporary accommodation for prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39708&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it appears to the Inspector`
  line `General that the number of prisoners in any prison is greater than can conveniently or safely be`
  line `kept therein, and it is not convenient to transfer the excess number to some other prison,`
  line
  line `or whenever from the outbreak of epidemic disease within any prison, or for any other reason, it is`
  line `desirable to provide for the temporary shelter and safe custody of any prisoners,`
  line
  line `provision shall be made, by such officer and in such manner as the State Government may`
  line `direct, for the shelter and safe custody in temporary prisons of so many of the prisoners as`
  line `cannot be conveniently or safely kept in the prison.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39709)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Control and duties of officers of prisons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "60".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39709&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `All officers of a prison shall obey the directions`
  line `of the Superintendent; all officers subordinate to the Jailer shall perform such duties as may be`
  line `imposed on them by the Jailer with the sanction of the Superintendent or be prescribed by rules`
  line `under section ^1[59].`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39710)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Officers not to have business dealings with prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39710&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No officer of a prison shall sell or`
  line `let, nor shall any person in trust for or employed by him sell or let, or derive any benefit from selling or`
  line `letting, any article to any prisoner or have any money or other business dealings, directly or indirectly,`
  line `with any prisoner.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39711)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers not to be interested in prison-contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39711&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No officer of a prison shall, nor`
  line `shall any person in trust for or employed by him, have any interest, direct or indirect, in any`
  line `contract for the supply of the prison : nor shall he derive any benefit, directly or indirectly, from`
  line `the sale or purchase of any article on behalf of the prison or belonging to a prisoner.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39712)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Superintendent.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39712&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the orders of the Inspector General, the Superintendent`
  line `shall manage the prison in all matters relating to discipline, labour, expenditure, punishment and`
  line control.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such general or special directions as may be given by the State Government, the`
  line `Superintendent of a prison other than a central prison or a prison situated in a presidency-town`
  line `shall obey all orders not inconsistent with this Act or any rule thereunder which may be given`
  line `respecting the prison by the District Magistrate, and shall report to the Inspector General all such`
  line `orders and the action taken thereon.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 11 of the principal Act, in sub-section (2), the words "a central prison or" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39713)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Records to be kept by Superintendent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1 The words and figures "or section 60" omitted by the A. O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39713&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Superintendent shall keep, or cause to be kept, the`
  line `following records :—`
  line
  line `(1) a register of prisoners admitted;`
  line
  line `(2) a book showing when each prisoner is to be released;`
  line
  line `(3) a punishment-book for the entry of the punishments inflicted on prisoners for prison-offences;`
  line
  line `(4) a visitors book for the entry of any observation made by the visitors touching any matters`
  line `connected with the administration of the prison;`
  line
  line `(5) a record of the money and other articles taken from prisoners;`
  line
  line `and all such other records as may be prescribed by rules under section 59 ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39714)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Duties of Medical Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39714&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the control of the Superintendent, the Medical Officer`
  line `shall have charge of the sanitary administration of the prison, and shall perform such ^1duties as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made by the State Government under section ^2[59].`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For rules as to Medical Officer's duties under s. 13, see different local Rules and Orders.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A O. 1937, for "60".`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39715)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Medical Officer to report in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39715&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Medical Officer has reason to`
  line `believe that the mind of a prisoner is, or is likely to be, injuriously affected by the discipline or treatment`
  line `to which he is subjected, the Medical Officer shall report the case in writing to the Superintendent,`
  line `together with such observations as he may think proper.`
  line
  line `This report, with the orders of the Superintendent thereon, shall forthwith be sent to the Inspector`
  line `General for information.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39716)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Report on death of prisoner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39716&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `On the death of any prisoner, the Medical Officer shall`
  line `forthwith record in a register the following particulars, so far as they can be ascertained, namely :--`
  line
  line `(1) the day on which the deceased first complained of illness or was observed to be ill,`
  line
  line `(2) the labour, if any, on which he was engaged on that day,`
  line
  line `(3) the scale of his diet on that day,`
  line
  line `(4) the day on which he was admitted to hospital,`
  line
  line `(5) the day on which the Medical Officer was first informed of the illness,`
  line
  line `(6) the nature of the disease,`
  line
  line `(7) when the deceased was last seen before his death by the Medical Officer or Medical`
  line Subordinate,
  line
  line `(8) when the prisoner died, and`
  line
  line `(9) (in cases where a post-mortem examination is made) an account of the appearances after death,`
  line
  line `together with any special remarks that appear to the Medical Officer to be required.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 15 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 15 of the principal Act, in clause (7), the words "or Medical Subordinate" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39717)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Jailer.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39717&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Jailer shall reside in the prison, unless the Superintendent permits him in writing`
  line `to reside elsewhere.`
  line
  line `(2) The Jailer shall not, without the Inspector General's sanction in writing, be concerned in any other`
  line employment.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39718)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Jailer to give notice of death of prisoner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39718&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Upon the death of a prisoner, the Jailer shall give`
  line `immediate notice thereof to the Superintendent and the Medical Subordinate.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 17 of the principal Act, for the words "Medical Subordinate" the words "Medical Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39719)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Responsibility of Jailer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39719&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Jailer shall be responsible for the safe custody of the records to`
  line `be kept under section 12, for the commitment warrants and all other documents confided to his care, and`
  line `for the money and other articles taken from prisoners.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39720)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Jailer to be present at night.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39720&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Jailer shall not be absent from the prison for a night`
  line `without permission in writing from the Superintendent but, if absent without leave for a night from`
  line `unavoidable necessity, he shall immediately report the fact and the cause of it to the Superintendent.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39721)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers of Deputy and Assistant Jailers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39721&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where a Deputy Jailer or Assistant Jailer is appointed`
  line `to a prison, he shall, subject to the orders of the Superintendent, be competent to perform any of the`
  line `duties, and be subject to all the responsibilities, of a Jailer under this Act or any rule thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39722)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Duties of gate-keeper.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39722&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The officer acting as gate-keeper, or any other officer of the prison, may`
  line `examine anything carried in or out of the prison, and may stop and search or cause to be searched any`
  line `person suspected of bringing any prohibited article into or out of the prison, or of carrying out any`
  line `property belonging to the prison, and, if any such article or property be found, shall give immediate notice`
  line `thereof to the Jailer.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39723)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Subordinate officers not to be absent without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39723&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Officers subordinate to the Jailer shall not`
  line `be absent from the prison without leave from the Superintendent or from the Jailer.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39724)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Convict officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39724&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Prisoners who have been appointed as officers of prisons shall be deemed to be`
  line `public servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39725)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Prisoners to be examined on admission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39725&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a prisoner is admitted into prison, he`
  line `shall be searched, and all weapons and prohibited articles shall be taken from him.`
  line
  line `(2) Every criminal prisoner shall also, as soon as possible after admission, be examined under the`
  line `general or special orders of the Medical Officer, who shall enter or cause to be entered in a book, to be`
  line `kept by the Jailer, a record of the state of the prisoner's health, and of any wounds or marks on his person,`
  line `the class of labour he is fit for if sentenced to rigorous imprisonment, and any observations which the`
  line `Medical Officer thinks fit to add.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of female prisoners the search and examination shall be carried out by the matron under`
  line `the general or special orders of the Medical Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39726)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Effects of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39726&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All money or other articles in respect whereof no order of a competent`
  line `Court has been made, and which may with proper authority be brought into the prison by any criminal`
  line `prisoner or sent to the prison for his use, shall be placed in the custody of the Jailer.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39727)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Removal and discharge of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39727&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) All prisoners, previously to being removed to any`
  line `other prison, shall be examined by the Medical Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) No prisoner shall be removed from one prison to another unless the Medical Officer certifies that`
  line `the prisoner is free from any illness rendering him unfit for removal.`
  line
  line `(3) No prisoner shall be discharged against his will from prison, if labouring under any acute or`
  line `dangerous distemper, nor until, in the opinion of the Medical Officer, such discharge is safe.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39728)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Separation of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 6 of 1930, s. 2, for "eighteen".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39728&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The requisitions of this Act with respect to the separation of prisoners`
  line `are as follows :—`
  line
  line `(1) in a prison containing female as well as male prisoners, the females shall be imprisoned in`
  line `separate buildings, or separate parts of the same building, in such manner as to prevent their seeing, or`
  line `conversing or holding any intercourse with, the male prisoners ;`
  line
  line `(2) in a prison where male prisoners under the age of ^1[twenty-one] are confined, means shall be`
  line `provided for separating them altogether from the other prisoners and for separating those of them who`
  line `have arrived at the age of puberty from those who have not;`
  line
  line `(3) unconvicted criminal prisoners shall be kept apart from convicted criminal`
  line `prisoners ; and`
  line
  line `(4) civil prisoners shall be kept apart from criminal prisoners.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39729)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Association and segregation of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39729&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the requirements of the last foregoing`
  line `section, convicted criminal prisoners may be confined either in association or individually in`
  line `cells or partly in one way and partly in the other.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39730)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Solitary confinement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39730&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No cell shall be used for solitary confinement unless it is furnished`
  line `with the means of enabling the prisoner to communicate at any time with an officer of the prison, and`
  line `every prisoner so confined in a cell for more than twenty-four hours, whether as a punishment or`
  line `otherwise, shall be visited at least once a day by the Medical Officer or Medical Subordinate.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 29 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 29 of the principal Act, for the words "or Medical Subordinate" the words "or any Officer authorised by the Medical Officer in this behalf" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1894, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39731)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Prisoners under sentence of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39731&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every prisoner under sentence of death shall,`
  line `immediately on his arrival in the prison after sentence, be searched by, or by order of, the Jailer and all`
  line `articles shall be taken from him which the Jailer deems it dangerous or inexpedient to leave in his`
  line possession.
  line
  line `(2) Every such prisoner shall be confined in a cell apart from all other prisoners, and shall be placed`
  line `by day and by night under the charge of a guard.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39732)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Maintenance of certain prisoners from private sources.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39732&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `A civil prisoner or an`
  line `unconvicted criminal prisoner shall be permitted to maintain himself, and to purchase, or receive from`
  line `private sources at proper hours, food, clothing, bedding or other necessaries, but subject to examination`
  line `and to such rules as may be approved by the Inspector General.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39733)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Restriction on transfer of food and clothing between certain prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39733&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No part of`
  line `any food, clothing, bedding or other necessaries belonging to any civil or unconvicted criminal prisoner`
  line `shall be given, hired or sold to any other prisoner ; and any prisoner transgressing the provisions of this`
  line `section shall lose the privilege of purchasing food or receiving it from private sources, for such time as`
  line `the Superintendent thinks proper.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39734)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Supply of clothing and bedding to civil and unconvicted criminal prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39734&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every civil prisoner and unconvicted prisoner unable to provide himself with sufficient clothing`
  line `and bedding shall be supplied by the Superintendent with such clothing and bedding as may be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(2) When any civil prisoner has been committed to prison in execution of a decree in favour`
  line `of a private person, such person, or his representative, shall, within forty-eight hours after the`
  line `receipt by him of a demand in writing, pay to the Superintendent the cost of the clothing and`
  line `bedding so supplied to the prisoner ; and in default of such payment the prisoner may be`
  line released.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39735)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Employment of civil prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39735&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Civil prisoners may, with the Superintendent's permission,`
  line `work and follow any trade or profession.`
  line
  line `(2) Civil prisoners finding their own implements, and not maintained at the expense of the prison,`
  line `shall be allowed to receive the whole of their earnings; but the earnings of such as are furnished with`
  line `implements or are maintained at the expense of the prison shall be subject to a deduction, to be`
  line `determined by the Superintendent, for the use of implements and the cost of maintenance.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39736)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Employment of criminal prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39736&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) No criminal prisoner sentenced to labour or`
  line `employed on labour at his own desire shall, except on an emergency with the sanction in writing of the`
  line `Superintendent, be kept to labour for more than nine hours in any one day.`
  line
  line `(2) The Medical Officer shall from time to time examine the labouring prisoners while they are`
  line `employed, and shall at least once in every fortnight cause to be recorded upon the history-ticket of each`
  line `prisoner employed on labour the weight of such prisoner at the time.`
  line
  line `(3) When the Medical Officer is of opinion that the health of any prisoner suffers from employment`
  line `on any kind or class of labour, such prisoner shall not be employed on that labour but shall be placed on`
  line `such other kind or class of labour as the Medical Officer may consider suited for him.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39737)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Employment of criminal prisoners sentenced to simple imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39737&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line Provision
  line `shall be made by the Superintendent for the employment (as long as they so desire) of all criminal`
  line `prisoners sentenced to simple imprisonment; but no prisoner not sentenced to rigorous imprisonment shall`
  line `be punished for neglect of work excepting by such alteration in the scale of diet as may be established by`
  line `the rules of the prison in the case of neglect of work by such a prisoner.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39738)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Sick prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39738&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The names of prisoners desiring to see the Medical Subordinate or`
  line `appearing out of health in mind or body shall, without delay, by reported by the officer in immediate`
  line `charge of such prisoners to the Jailer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Jailer shall, without delay, call the attention of the Medical Subordinate to any prisoners`
  line `desiring to see him, or who is ill, or whose state of mind or body appears to require attention, and shall`
  line `carry into effect all written directions given by the Medical Officer or Medical Subordinate respecting`
  line `alterations of the discipline or treatment of any such prisoner.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 37 of Act IX of 1894.--(1) in sub-section (1), for the words "Medical Subordinate" the words "Medical Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(2) In sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "Medical Subordinate", where they occur for the first time, the words "Medical Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) the words "or Medical Subordinate" shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39739)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Record of directions of Medical Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39739&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `All directions given by the Medical Officer or`
  line `Medical Subordinate in relation to any prisoner, with the exception of orders for the supply of medicines`
  line `or directions relating to such matters as are carried into effect by the Medical Officer himself or under his`
  line `superintendence, shall be entered day by day in the prisoner's history-ticket or in such other record as the`
  line `State Government may by rule direct, and the Jailer shall make an entry in its proper place stating in`
  line `respect of each direction the fact of its having been or not having been complied with, accompanied by`
  line `such observations, if any, as the Jailer thinks fit to make, and the date of the entry.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 38 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 38 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(1) the words "or Medical Subordinate" shall be deleted;`
  line
  line `(2) in the marginal note, for the word "Officers" the word "Officer" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XLV of 1959, s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (39740)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title Hospital.
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39740&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `In every prison an hospital or proper place for the reception of sick prisoners shall be`
  line provided.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (39741)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Visits to civil and unconvicted criminal prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39741&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Due provision shall be made for`
  line `the admission, at proper times and under proper restrictions, into every prison of persons with`
  line `whom civil or unconvicted criminal prisoners may desire to communicate, care being taken that`
  line `so far as may be consistent with the interests of justice, prisoners under trial may see their duly`
  line `qualified legal advisers without the presence of any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (39742)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Search of visitors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39742&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Jailer may demand the name and address of any visitor to prisoner,`
  line `and, when the Jailer has any ground for suspicion, may search any visitor, or cause him to be searched,`
  line `but the search shall not be made in the presence of any prisoner or of another visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of any such visitor refusing to permit himself to be searched, the Jailer may deny him`
  line `admission; and the grounds of such proceeding, with the particulars thereof, shall be entered in such`
  line `record as the State Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (39764)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Penalty for introduction or removal of prohibited articles into or from prison and communication with prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A. O, 1937, for "60".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39764&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, contrary to any rule under section ^1[59] introduces`
  line `or removes or attempts by any means whatever to introduce or remove, into or from any prison,`
  line `or supplies or attempts to supply to any prisoner outside the limits of a prison, any prohibited`
  line article,
  line
  line `and every officer of a prison who, contrary to any such rule, knowingly suffers any such article to be`
  line `introduced into or removed from any prison, to be possessed by any prisoner, or to be supplied to any`
  line `prisoner outside the limits of a prison,`
  line
  line `and whoever, contrary to any such rule, communicates or attempts to communicate with any`
  line prisoner,
  line
  line `and whoever abets any offence made punishable by this section,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be liable to imprisonment for a term not exceeding six`
  line `months, or to fine not exceeding two hundred rupees, or to both.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39744)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to arrest for offence under section.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39744&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `When any person, in the presence of any`
  line `officer of a prison, commits any offence specified in the last foregoing section, and refuses on`
  line `demand of such officer to state his name and residence, or gives a name or residence which such`
  line `officer knows, or has reason to believe, to be false, such officer may arrest him, and shall`
  line `without unnecessary delay make him over to a Police-officer, and thereupon such Police-officer`
  line `shall proceed as if the offence had been committed in his presence.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39745)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Publication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39745&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Superintendent shall cause to be affixed, in a conspicuous`
  line `place outside the prison, a notice in English and the Vernacular setting forth the acts`
  line `prohibited under section 42 and the penalties incurred by their commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39746)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title Prison-offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39746&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The following acts are declared to be prison-offences when committed by a`
  line `prisoner :—`
  line
  line `(1) such wilful disobedience to any regulation of the prison as shall have been declared by rules`
  line `made under section 59 to be a prison-offence ;`
  line
  line `(2) any assault or use of criminal force ;`
  line
  line `(3) the use of insulting or threatening language ;`
  line
  line `(4) immoral or indecent or disorderly behaviour ;`
  line
  line `(5) wilfully disabling himself from labour ;`
  line
  line `(6) contumaciously refusing to work ;`
  line
  line `(7) filling, cutting, altering or removing handcuffs, fetters or bars without due authority ;`
  line
  line `(8) wilful idleness or negligence at work by any prisoner sentenced to rigorous imprisonment ;`
  line
  line `(9) wilful mismanagement of work by any prisoner sentenced to rigorous imprisonment ;`
  line
  line `(10) wilful damage to prison-property ;`
  line
  line `(11) tampering with or defacing history-tickets, records or documents ;`
  line
  line `(12) receiving, possessing or transferring any prohibited article ;`
  line
  line `(13) feigning illness ;`
  line
  line `(14) wilfully bringing a false accusation against any officer or prisoner ;`
  line
  line `(15) omitting or refusing to report, as soon as it comes to his knowledge, the occurrence of any`
  line `fire, any plot or conspiracy, any escape, attempt or preparation to escape, and any attack or`
  line `preparation for attack upon any prisoner or prison-official ; and`
  line
  line `(16) conspiring to escape, or to assist in escaping, or to commit any other of the offences`
  line aforesaid.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39747)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Punishment of such offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39747&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `^146. Punishment of such offences.--The Superintendent may examine any person to`
  line `touching any such offence, and determine thereupon, and punish such offence by--`
  line
  line `(1) a formal warning :`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A formal warning shall mean a warning personally addressed to a prisoner by the`
  line `Superintendent and recorded in the punishment-book and on the prisoner's history-ticket ;`
  line
  line `(2) change of labour to some more irksome or severe form ^2[for such period as may be prescribed`
  line `by rules made by the ^3[State Government]] ;`
  line
  line `(3) hard labour for a period not exceeding seven days in the case of convicted criminal prisoners`
  line `not sentenced to rigorous imprisonment ;`
  line
  line `(4) such loss of privileges admissible under the remission system for the time being in force as`
  line `may be prescribed by rules made by the ^3[State Government ];`
  line
  line `(5) the substitution of gunny or other coarse fabric for clothing of other material, not being`
  line `woollen, for a period which shall not exceed three months ;`
  line
  line `(6) imposition of handcuffs of such pattern and weight, in such manner and for such period, as may`
  line `be prescribed by rules made by the ^3[State Government] ;`
  line
  line `(7) imposition of fetters of such pattern and weight, in such manner and for such period, as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made by the ^3[State Government] ;`
  line
  line `(8) separate confinement for any period not exceeding ^4[three] months ;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Separate confinement means such confinement with or without labour as`
  line `secludes a prisoner from communication with, but not from sight of, other prisoners, and allows`
  line `him not less than one hour's exercise per diem and to have his meals in association with one or`
  line `more other prisoners ;`
  line
  line `(9) penal diet,--that is, restriction of diet in such manner and subject to such conditions regarding`
  line `labour as may be prescribed by the State Government :`
  line
  line `Provided that such restriction of diet shall in no case be applied to a prisoner for more than ninety-six`
  line `consecutive hours, and shall not be repeated except for a fresh offence nor until after an interval of`
  line `one week ;`
  line
  line `(10) cellular confinement for any period not exceeding fourteen days :`
  line
  line `Provided that after each period of cellular confinement an interval of not less duration than such`
  line `period must elapse before the prisoner is again sentenced to cellular or solitary confinement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Cellular confinement means such confinement with or without labour as entirely`
  line `secludes a prisoner from communication with, but not from sight of, other prisoners ;`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^6[(11)] penal diet as defined in clause (9) combined with ^7[cellular] confinement ^8***;`
  line
  line `^6[(12)] whipping, provided that the number of stripes shall not exceed thirty :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall render any female or civil prisoner liable to the imposition`
  line `of any form of handcuffs or fetters, or to whipping.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46 of Act 9 of 1894.--(1) In Section 46 of the Principal Act, clause (12) and the words "or to whipping" appearing in the proviso to the said section shall be omitted and a full stop shall be substituted for the comma appearing after the word "fetter" in the said proviso.`
  line
  line `(2) In section 46 of the Principal Act, add the following clauses after clause (11), namely: --`
  line
  line `" (12) forfeiture of class, grade, or prison privileges for a period not exceeding three months;`
  line
  line `(13) permanent or temporary reduction from a higher to a lower class or grade".`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 12 of 1956, s. 2.]`
  line
  line Orissa.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46 (Act 9 of 1894).--In section 46 of the said Act--`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (4) for the words the remission system the words the remission or furlough system shall`
  line `be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) clause (5) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 29 of 1958, s. 3].`
  line
  line Orissa.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46 (Act 9 of 1894).--In section 46 of the Prisons Act, 1894 (9 of 1894), after`
  line `clause (4) the following new clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(4-a) temporary forfeiture of class, grade or prison-privileges or temporary or permanent reduction from a`
  line `higher to a lower class or grade.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 23 of 1956, s. 2]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 46 of the said Act, in clause (4), for the`
  line `words "the remission system" the words "the remission or furlough system" shall be substituted".`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1953, s. 3].`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For rules issued with reference to clauses (4), (6) and (7) of section 46 see Gazette of India, 1923, Pt. 1, p. 1751.`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 17 of 1925, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "G. G. in C."`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 17 of 1925, s. 2, for "six".`
  line
  line `5. Clause (11) omitted by Act 17 of 1925, s. 2.`
  line
  line `6. Clauses (12) and (13) renumbered as clauses (11) and (12) respectively by s. 2, ibid.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "solitary."`
  line
  line `8. The words "as defined in clause (11)" omitted by s. 2, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39748)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Plurality of punishments under section 46.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39748&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Any two of the punishments`
  line `enumerated in the last foregoing section may be awarded for any such offence in combination,`
  line `subject to the following exceptions, namely :`
  line
  line `(1) formal warning shall not be combined with any other punishment except loss of privileges`
  line `under clause (4) of that section ;`
  line
  line `(2) penal diet shall not be combined with change of labour under clause (2) of that section, nor`
  line `shall any additional period of penal diet awarded singly be combined with any period of penal diet`
  line `awarded in combination with ^2[cellular] confinement ;`
  line
  line `^3[(3) cellular confinement shall not he combined with separate confinement, so as to prolong the`
  line `total period of seclusion to which the prisoner shall be liable ;]`
  line
  line `(4) whipping shall not be combined with any other form of punishment except cellular`
  line `^4[and] separate confinement and loss of privileges admissible under the remission system ;`
  line
  line `^5[(5) no punishment will be combined with any other punishment in contravention of rules made by`
  line `the ^6[State Government]]`
  line
  line `^7](2) No punishment shall be awarded for any such offence so as to combine, with the punishment`
  line `awarded for any other such offence two of the punishment which may not be awarded in combination for`
  line `any such offence.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam.
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 47 of Act IX of 1894.--In sub-section (1) of section 47 of the Principal Act, clause (4) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 12 of 1956, s. 3.]`
  line
  line Orissa.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47 (Act 9 of 1894).--In section 47 of the said Act, in clause (4) of`
  line `sub-section (1) for the words "the remission system " the words "the remission or furlough system" shall`
  line `be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 29 of 1958, s. 4]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 47 of the said act, in clause (4) of subsection (1), for the words "the remission system " the words "the remission or furlough system " shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1953, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 47 re-numbered as sub-section (1) of section 47, by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "solitary ".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for exception (3).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for "or ".`
  line
  line `5. Added by Act 17 of 1925, s. 3.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "G.G. in C. ".`
  line
  line `7. Added by Act 17 of 1925, s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39749)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Award of punishments under sections 46 and 47.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39749&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Superintendent shall have power to`
  line `award any of the punishments enumerated in the two last foregoing sections, subject, in the case of`
  line `separate confinement for a period exceeding one month, to the previous confirmation of the Inspector`
  line General.
  line
  line `(2) No officer subordinate to the Superintendent shall have power to award any punishment whatever.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 48-A (Act 9 of 1894).--After section 48 of the said Act, the following new`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `48-A. Punishment for breach of conditions of suspension of sentence.--If any prisoner fails`
  line `without sufficient cause to observe any of the conditions on which his sentence was suspended or`
  line `remitted or furlough was granted to him, he shall be deemed to have committed a prison offence and the`
  line `Superintendent may after obtaining his explanation, punish such offence by--`
  line
  line `(1) a formal warning as provided in clause (1) of section 46; or`
  line
  line `(2) Reduction in grade if such prisoner has been appointed as an officer of prison; or`
  line
  line `(3) Loss of privileges admissible under the remission or furlough system; or`
  line
  line `(4) Loss of such other privileges as the State Government may, by a general or special order direct.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 29 of 1958. s. 5].`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `After section 48 of the said Act, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--Insertion of`
  line `section 48A in act IX of 1894.--`
  line
  line `"48A. Punishment for breach of conditions of suspension of sentence, etc.--If any prisoner`
  line `fails without sufficient cause to observe any of the conditions on which his sentence was suspended`
  line `or remitted or furlough was granted to him, he shall be deemed to have committed a prison offence`
  line `and the superintendent may, after obtaining his explanation, punish such offence by--`
  line
  line `(1) a formal warning as provided in clause (1) of section 46;`
  line
  line `(2) reduction in grade if such prisoner has been appointed or furlough system; or`
  line
  line `(3) loss of privileges admissible under the remission or furlough system; or`
  line
  line `(4) loss of such other privileges as the state Government may by a general or special order`
  line `direct."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1953, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (39750)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Punishments to be in accordance with foregoing sections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39750&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Except by order of a Court of`
  line `Justice, no punishment other than the punishments specified in the foregoing sections shall be inflicted on`
  line `any prisoner, and no punishment shall be inflicted on any prisoner otherwise than in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of those sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (39751)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Medical Officer to certify to fitness of prisoner for punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39751&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) No punishment of penal`
  line `diet, either singly or in combination, or of whipping, or of change of labour under section 46, clause (2),`
  line `shall be executed until the prisoner to whom such punishment has been awarded has been examined by`
  line `the Medical Officer, who, if he considers the prisoner fit to undergo the punishment, shall certify`
  line `accordingly in the appropriate column of the punishment-book prescribed in section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) If he considers the prisoner unfit to undergo the punishment, he shall in like manner record his`
  line `opinion in writing and shall state whether the prisoner is absolutely unfit for punishment of the kind`
  line `awarded, or whether he considers any modification necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) In the latter case he shall state what extent of punishment he thinks the prisoner can undergo`
  line `without injury to his health.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam.
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 50 of Act 9 of 1894.--In sub-section (1) of section 50 of the Principal Act the words and comma “or of whipping,” shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 12 of 1956, s. 4.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (39752)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Entries in punishment-books.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39752&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the punishment-book prescribed in section 12 there shall`
  line `be recorded, in respect of every punishment inflicted, the prisoner's name, register number and the class`
  line `(whether habitual or not) to which he belongs, the prison-offence of which he was guilty, the date on`
  line `which such prison-offence was committed, the number of previous prison-offences recorded against the`
  line `prisoner, and the date of his last prison-offence, the punishment awarded, and the date of infliction.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of every serious prison-offence, the names of the witnesses proving the offence shall`
  line `be recorded, and, in the case of offences for which whipping is awarded, the Superintendent shall record`
  line `the substance of the evidence of the witnesses, the defence of the prisoner, and the finding with the`
  line `reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(3) Against the entries relating to each punishment the Jailor and Superintendent shall affix their`
  line `initials as evidence of the correctness of the entries.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam.
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 51 of Act 9 of 1894.--.In sub-section (2) of Section 51 of the Principal Act the words “in the words “in the cases of offences for which whipping is awarded” and the commas before this words and thereafter shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 12 of 1956, s. 5.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (39753)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Procedure on committal of heinous offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39753&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If any prisoner is guilty of any offence`
  line `against prison-discipline which, by reason of his having frequently committed such offences or`
  line `otherwise, in the opinion of the Superintendent, is not adequately punishable by the infliction of any`
  line `punishment which he has power under this Act to award, the Superintendent may forward such`
  line `prisoner to the Court of the District Magistrate or of any Magistrate of the first class ^1[or Presidency`
  line `Magistrate] having jurisdiction, together with a statement of the circumstances, and such Magistrate`
  line `shall thereupon inquire into and try the charge so brought against the prisoner, and, upon conviction,`
  line `may sentence him to imprisonment which may extend to one year, such term to be in addition to any`
  line `term for which such prisoner was undergoing imprisonment when he committed such offence, or`
  line `may sentence him to any of the punishments enumerated in section 46 :`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that any such case may be transferred for inquiry and trial by the District Magistrate to any`
  line `Magistrate of the first class and by a Chief Presidency Magistrate to any other Presidency Magistrate :`
  line and]
  line
  line `Provided also that no person shall be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . Ins. by Act 13 of 1910, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for the proviso.`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (39754)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title Whipping.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39754&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) No punishment of whipping shall be inflicted in instalments, or except in the`
  line `presence of the Superintendent and Medical Officer or Medical Subordinate.`
  line
  line `(2) Whipping shall be inflicted with a light ratan not less than half an inch in diameter on the`
  line `buttocks, and in case of prisoners under the age of sixteen it shall be inflicted, in the way of school`
  line `discipline, with a lighter ratan.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam.
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 53 of Act 9 of 1894.--Section 53 of the Principal Act shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 12 of 1956, s. 6.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (39755)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Offences by prison-subordinates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39755&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Jailor or officer of a prison subordinate to him`
  line `who shall be guilty of any violation of duty or wilful breach or neglect of any rule or regulation or lawful`
  line `order made by competent authority, or who shall withdraw from the duties of his office without`
  line `permission, or without having given previous notice in writing of his intention for the period of two`
  line `months, or who shall wilfully overstay any leave granted to him, or who shall engage without authority in`
  line
  line `any employment other than his prison-duty, or who shall be guilty of cowardice, shall be liable, on`
  line `conviction before a Magistrate, to fine not exceeding two hundred rupees, or to imprisonment for a period`
  line `not exceeding three months, or to both.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall under this section be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (39756)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Extramural custody, control and employment of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39756&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `A prisoner, when being taken to`
  line `or from any prison in which he may be lawfully confined, or whenever he is working outside or is`
  line `otherwise beyond the limits of any such prison in or under the lawful custody or control of a prisonofficer`
  line `belonging to such person, shall be deemed to be in prison and shall be subject to all the same`
  line `incidents as if he were actually in prison.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (39757)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Confinement in irons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39757&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Superintendent considers it necessary (with reference`
  line `either to the state of the prison or the character of the prisoners) for the safe custody of any prisoners that`
  line `they should be confined in irons, he may, subject to such rules and instructions as may be laid down by`
  line `the Inspector General with the sanction of the State Government, so confine them.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (39758)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Confinement of prisoners under sentence of transportation in irons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "60".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39758&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Prisoners under`
  line `sentence of transportation may, subject to any rules made under section ^1[59], be confined in fetters for`
  line `the first three months after admission to prison.`
  line
  line `(2) Should the Superintendent consider it necessary, either for the safe custody of the prisoner`
  line `himself or for any other reason, that fetters should be retained on any such prisoner for more than three`
  line `months, he shall apply to the Inspector General for sanction to their retention for the period for which he`
  line `considers their retention necessary, and the Inspector General may sanction such retention accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (39759)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Prisoners not to be ironed by Jailer except under necessity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39759&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `No prisoner shall be put`
  line `in irons or under mechanical restraint by the Jailer of his own authority, except in case of urgent`
  line `necessity, in which case notice thereof shall be forthwith given to the Superintendent.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (39760)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39760&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] ^2[The State Government may] ^3[by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette] make rules consistent with this Act--`
  line
  line `(1) defining the acts which shall constitute prison-offences ;`
  line
  line `(2) determining the classification of prison-offences into serious and minor offences;`
  line
  line `(3) fixing the punishments admissible under this Act which shall be awardable for commission of`
  line `prison-offences or classes thereof ;`
  line
  line `(4) declaring the circumstances in which acts constituting both a prison-offence and an`
  line `offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) may or may not be dealt with as a prisonoffence ;`
  line
  line `(5) for the award of marks and the shortening of sentences ;`
  line
  line `(6) regulating the use of arms against any prisoner or body of prisoners in the case of an outbreak`
  line `or attempt to escape ;`
  line
  line `(7) defining the circumstances and regulating the conditions under which prisoners in danger of`
  line `death may be released ;`
  line
  line `^4[(8) for the classification of prisons, and description and construction of wards, cells and other`
  line `places of detention;`
  line
  line `(9) for the regulation by numbers, length or character of sentences, or otherwise, of the prisoners to`
  line `be confined in each class of prisons;`
  line
  line `(10) for the government of prisons and for the appointment of all officers appointed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(11) as to the food, bedding and clothing of criminal prisoners and of civil prisoners maintained`
  line `otherwise than at their own cost;`
  line
  line `(12) for the employment, instruction and control of convicts within or without prisons;`
  line
  line `(13) for defining articles the introduction or removal of which into or out of prisons without due`
  line `authority is prohibited;`
  line
  line `(14) for classifying and prescribing the forms of labour and regulating the periods of rest from`
  line labour;
  line
  line `(15) for regulating the disposal of the proceeds of the employment of prisoners;`
  line
  line `(16) for regulating the confinement in fetters of prisoners sentenced to transportation;`
  line
  line `(17) for the classification and the separation of prisoners;`
  line
  line `(18) for regulating the confinement of convicted criminal prisoners under section 28;`
  line
  line `(19) for the preparation and maintenance of history-tickets;`
  line
  line `(20) for the selection and appointment of prisoners as officers of prisons;`
  line
  line `(21) for rewards for good conduct;`
  line
  line `(22) for regulating the transfer of prisoners whose term of transportation or imprisonment is about`
  line `to expire subject, however, to the consent of the State Government of any other State to which a`
  line `prisoner is to be transferred;`
  line
  line `(23) for the treatment, transfer and disposal of criminal lunatics or recovered criminal lunatics`
  line `confined in prisons;`
  line
  line `(24) for regulating the transmission of appeals and petitions from prisoners and their`
  line `communications with their friends;`
  line
  line `(25) for the appointment and guidance of visitors of prisons;`
  line
  line `(26) for extending any or all of the provisions of this Act and of the rules thereunder to`
  line `subsidiary jails or special places of confinement appointed under section 541 of the ^5Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1882 (10 of 1882), and to the officers employed, and the prisoners`
  line `confined, therein;`
  line
  line `(27) in regard to the admission, custody, employment, dieting, treatment and release of prisoners;`
  line and
  line
  line `(28) generally for carrying into effect the purposes of this Act.]`
  line
  line `^6[(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the`
  line `State Legislature.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 59 (Act 9 of 1894).--In section 59 of the said Act, for clause (5) the`
  line `following clause shall be substitute, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) for the award of marks, granting remission or furlough, determining the conditions on`
  line `which and the authority by which such remission or furlough shall be granted and the`
  line `consequent shortening of the sentence."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Orissa Act 29 of 1958, s.6]`
  line
  line Maharashtra.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 59 of Act IX of 1894.--In section 59 of the said Act, for clause (5), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) for the award of marks, granting remission or furlough, determining the conditions on which`
  line `and the authority by which such remission or furlough shall be granted and the consequent shortening`
  line `of the sentence."`
  line
  line `[Vide Bombay Act XXVII of 1953, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 59 renumbered as sub-section (1) by the Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "The G.G. in C. may for any part of British India, and each L.G. with the previous sanction of the`
  line `G.G in C. may for the territories under its administration".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for clauses (8) and (9).`
  line
  line `5. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (Act 2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986 s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (39761)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title [Repealed.].
  content `^160.[Power of Local Government to make rules.] Rep. by the A. O. 1937.`
  footnotes `1. This section has been incorporated with slight modifications in clauses (8) to (27) of s. 59.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39761&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (39762)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Exhibition of copies of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "sections 59 and 60".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39762&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Copies of rules, under ^1[section 59] so far as they affect`
  line `the government of prisons, shall be exhibited, both in English and in the Vernacular, in some`
  line `place to which all persons employed within a prison have access.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (39763)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Exercise of powers of Superintendent and Medical Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866&sectionId=39763&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00063_189409_1523337412866
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `All or any of the powers`
  line `and duties conferred and imposed by this Act on a Superintendent or Medical Officer may in his absence`
  line `be exercised and performed by such other officer as the State Government may appoint in this behalf`
  line `either by name or by his official designation.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
